					<p class="STYLE1"><strong>LI Dayong</strong><br>
		    Male,  born in May 1958, Ph.D., Professor, Ph.D. Supervisor, President</p>		
		  <p><strong>Educational Background</strong><br>
		    Sep. 1978  - July 1982,Harbin University of Science and Technology, majoring in the Craft and Equipment of Foundry,  Bachelor.<br>
		    Sep. 1984  - July 1987, Harbin University of Science and Technology, majoring in Foundry, Master.<br>
		    Mar. 1997  - Dec. 1999, Harbin Institute of Technology,  majoring in Material Processing Engineering, Ph.D.<br>
		    Dec. 2004  - Dec. 2005, University of Sheffield, U. K., Visiting Scholar.</p>
		  <p><strong>Working Experiences</strong><br>
		    July 1982  - Aug. 1995, Harbin University of Science and Technology, Teaching Assistant, Lecturer,  Associate Professor, Associate Dean, Dean. <br>
		    Sep. 1995  - , Harbin University of Science and Technology, Professor, Dean, Vice President,  President.<br>
		    <br>
  <strong>Research Interests and Expertise</strong><br>
		    Prof. LI Dayong has been engaged in the  research of the Technology of Fast Detection and Automatic Control of Materials  Processing, Technology of Health Monitoring of Materials and Equipments. In recent  years, he has been giving such lectures to both undergraduates and graduates as  Mechanization of Foundry, Application of Micro-computer in Foundry, Measurement  of the Non-electrical Quantity in Foundry, Technology of Fast Measurement of  the Parameters in Foundry Production, New Technology of Forming of the Advanced  Materials and the Development of the Science of Materials. His teaching  has received good response from students and has achieved good teaching  effects.</p>
		  <p><strong>Academic Achievements</strong> <br>
		    Prof. LI has  been engaged in the teaching and research on fast measurement and control in  materials processing. He has chaired more than twenty projects, such as the National  Natural Sciences Fund — Scientific Instruments Program, the National Natural Sciences  Fund, the Excellent Youth Funde,  the Fund for Returned Overseas Scholars of Heilongjiang Province, the Fund of  Trans-Century Discipline Leaders of Machinery Ministry, Science and Technology  Fund of Machinery Ministry,  Heilongjiang Province, Heilongjiang Natural Science Fund, Science  Fund for Youths of Heilongjiang, the Key Scientific and Technological Project  of Harbin, the Fund for Excellent Discipline Leaders of Harbin, the Fund for  Youths of Harbin, the Fund for Publishing Excellent  Textbooks of Harbin, and the enterprise<strong> </strong>entrustment research projects. Besides, Prof. LI has won the second  prize of  of  Machinery Ministry of China, the third prize of Science and Technology Progress  Award of Heilongjiang, Excellent Textbook Award of Heilongjiang Province, four  national invention patents, and three new practical patents. Prof. LI has  published one monograph and one textbook and is the author of more than one  hundred and twenty academic papers, many of which have been indexed in EI and  SCI.<br>
  <strong>Honors and Awards</strong><br>
		    Prof. LI is  one of the State Candidates of Millions of Talents Project of the New Century. He  is the winner of national government subsidy, Excellent Youth Fund of Heilongjiang,  a provincial key discipline leader of Heilongjiang, a executive director in the  National Foundry Association, Chairman of the National Foundry Equipment and  Technology Committee, Chairman of Harbin Foundry Committee, a member of  Technological Economic Advisory Committee of Heilongjiang, Chairman of Harbin Scientific  Association, and a member of Harbin Expert Advisory Committee. Prof. LI is also  an editor of “the Journal of Mechanical Engineering”, “Chinese Journal of Mechanical  Engineering”, “China Foundry”, “China Mechanical Engineering”, “Foundry”, “China  Foundry Equipment and Technology”, etc.</p>
